task.summary: Default task
Structural changes and implementations like JavaFX, JUnit, Camunda, jSerialComm and exemplary code.
Additions to the pom.xml and the creation of a README.md.
New Structuring of the MainApplication.java and the creation/integration of UML.png.
Redesign of the BPMN environment and handling. The pom.xml is now more lightweight but the user need`s to implement a separate Camunda Modeler App.
Clean-up in the program and ready to merge to the main branch.
JavaFX experimentations and first integrations. It was also changed to use SceneBuilder for operating designs.
Scene Creator frontend/layout modifications and first style changes.

The scene was adjusted and complemented. There is also a separate Admin Scene. The code is more lightweight now and reduces duplicates as much as possible. Warning: The Admin page does have a problem with the scroll function. The belief is, that it is an error in JavaFX and not in our application.

The frontend is extended with further functionality. The Camunda Modeler files are included and the app opens by request. Files Long-Run and Short-Run are not complete, but that needs to be done if we now how and what to control at the engine. The application is running and the warnings are acceptable. The admin page is added but not configured at all.

The data processing does include all new objects and classes needed to order the Process Data for further investigation and operations. As an addition, Unversioned Files appeared which could have an impact in the further process but could also just include technical changes!

The data processing is for the first part complete. It was tested lightweight via prints. The result is a data type tree structure, including all the information directly or with code numbers. All in all, it is ready to go to the pm are for analysis and hardware preparation.
Small changes and actualisation's in the UML.svg file for the transparency.
Addendum/Improvement: We forgot to implement the Gateway node. As a result, did we add it to all areas where needed and we adjusted the UML diagram as well.
Addendum/Improvement: Logical adjustment in the sense of accepting Exclusive gateways, with specific rules, for easier loop handling.

Process Mining and advanced! The goal was to implement the pm package but the data was unclear. This session resulted in an overall session including changes in nearly all related areas. Most important we got the hardware running and data printing!
Adjustments related to the lates chaotic commit (push). More style and logical adjustments.
Small Admin adjustments and logical structuring.
Small Admin adjustments and form related contributions to reduce errors.
Adjustments to warnings and the change of Camunda Modeler opener method to eliminate the warnings and to modernize the API.

Big steps into the data saving, loading and changing of .txt data. Adjustments to the admin frontend and the handling of those new options. The Connection area got bigger for the moment but will be orders in the next time.
Untested Changes to the data processing and file creation of the blueprint data. Adding of an additional variable for the analyses of the processed missions.
Tested file writing functions and return data ordering. Out-commenting is temporary for reasons of easier testing.
Adjustment of the latest changes to the UML diagram.
Changes to the clean structure and visualisation. No rudimentary changes but rather a cleanup for the presentation to the coordinator. Last push before the exams brake.
Changes and clean up for a clean rebuild of the new branch.
Creation of THE SWITCH - PREP, to adjust the code and its structure for the rebuilding phase including a new Process Modeler.
First changes to the frontend structure and the inclusion of the Process JavaFX interface. Still not working but we consider a first save for refactoring.
Partly working web view with the wrong browser. The Overall view is correct.
The main change of The Switch, with changes of the data receiving and data processing. It still needs a lot of changes and especially testing.
Adjustments and further changes which are a result of the new modeler. The Terminal and the blueprint was adjusted as well.
UML adjustments for the correct documentation.
Changes doe to new ideas for the model representation and preparation for the analyses start.
ReadMe adjustments recording to the new changes.
Preparation for the analysis phase.
Major changes to the blueprint aspect and the creation of a corresponding command file for the admin blueprint initialisation.
The data comparison and saving is adjusted and build. The next phase is the reals Checking of the compliance and its savings in a meaningful manner.
IN the middle of the sensor data per second comparison and shortly before the mathematical evaluation.
Major changes to the User Scene with the adding of customizable deviation and acceptance.
Final implementations and adjustments to the calculation of the compliance checking. -> Compliance Checking Algorithm.
User Interface adjustments: Selection increase, Process Creation, Process Visualization, Test Result structure. First Test for the data gathering are started in a not engine like manner.
First serialisation tests and adjustments to the hardware.
Adjustments and new structures after FIRST PRACTICAL TESTS. Admin side with complete practical tests. New structure in data analyses and processing.
